CatDescriptText: Mrs. Eva Bonner, housewife, 6303 Dean Street., was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 10, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "How do you think Soviet Premier Khrushchev's visit to the United States affected relations between our country and Russia? Were you or were you not impressed by his visit to Pittsburgh?" answer reads: "I think there has been a change for the better."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Eva Bonner, wearing light colored short sleeved sweater, herringbone skirt, and round pendant necklace, standing on Liberty Avenue, in front of Jenkins Arcade with haberdashers store, Downtown
